    <center><table class="itemDisplayTable">
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Title:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Heart Beat Driven Intravenous Fluid Injection Control</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Authors:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Ruby Mishra, Raveesha Singh</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Keywords:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Heart Beat Driven<br />Intravenous Fluid Injection Control</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Issue Date:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">May-2012 </td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Publisher:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">SRM University</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Series/Report no.:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">P5483</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Abstract:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Our project mainly gives the implementation of a simple heart beat driven stepper motor. We are recording various parameters- Temperature, Pressure and Heart Beat Rate and analyzing this data using LabVIEW. For various purposes like during Operation of major part of body, dehydration, chemotherapy, we need regular information regarding body parameters and their values.
The Labview panel of the project shows the heart-beat per minute, temperature and pressure. The project is consists of sensing elements, a voltage regulator, an interfacing module, a stepper motor with its drive .Heart beat is sensed by the sensing elements and the comparator produces an amplified square wave output. The comparator output is given to a low pass filter and the filter output is fed to one of the digital inputs of PIC 16F877a type of micro controller. The micro controller output ports drive stepper motor drive and interfacing sysytem.
After recording this information, we are transferring this data using RS232. All this is being done using LabVIEW, which is faster and more efficient software.
This paper describes the design of a very low-cost device which measures the heart rate of the subject by clipping sensors on one of the ear and then displaying the result on monitor using Labview. Advantage of such a design is that it can be expanded and can easily be connected to an Intravenous fluid injector using a valve which will control the fluid injected inside the human body and analyse the data for over a period of time.
Heart rate measurement is one of the very important parameters of the human cardiovascular system. The heart rate of a healthy adult at rest is around 72 beats per minute (bpm). Athletes normally have lower heart rates than less active people. Babies have a much higher heart rate at around 120 bpm, while older children have heart rates at around 90 bpm. The heart rate rises gradually during exercises and returns slowly to the rest value after exercise. The rate when the pulse returns to normal is an indication of the fitness of the person</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">URI:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue"><a href="http://hdl.handle.net/123456789/9503">http://hdl.handle.net/123456789/9503</a></td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Appears in Collections:</td><td class="metadataFieldValue"><a href="/dspace/handle/123456789/8706">ICE-2012</a><br/></td></tr>
